The paper deals with formalizing common sense for scalable inconsistency robust information integration, which is a topic that falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces Direct Logic, which is a minimal fix to classical mathematical logic, and discusses its contributions over previous work, which falls under the scope of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions sense making for natural language, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the Actor Model, which is a model of concurrent computation, and its use in proving that Logic Programming is not computationally universal, which falls under the scope of databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE).
